<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FF85FFCFA7ADFE92FA80DDEF" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="0755A263FF85FFCFA7ADFE92FEB8DD96" blockId="28.[189,382,381,407]" box="[189,382,381,407]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<heading id="5C1D150FFF85FFCFA7ADFE92FEB8DD96" bold="true" box="[189,382,381,407]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF85FFCFA7ADFE92FEB8DD96" bold="true" box="[189,382,381,407]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Natural history</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF85FFCFA7ADFE41FA80DDEF" blockId="28.[189,1398,430,495]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Specimens were collected under a rock of volcanic tuff, with a juvenile of the scorpion 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF85FFCFA3A8FE41FE0EDDEF" authority="Teruel &amp; Chazal, 2010" authorityName="Teruel &amp; Chazal" authorityYear="2010" class="Arachnida" family="Diplocentridae" genus="Oiclus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nanus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF85FFCFA3A8FE41FAC3DDC9" box="[1208,1285,430,456]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Oiclus</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF85FFCFA220FE40FAB0DDC9" box="[1328,1398,431,456]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">nanus</emphasis>
Teruel &amp; Chazal, 2010
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF85FFCFA6C7FE3BFD4BDDEE" authorityName="Karsch" authorityYear="1880" box="[471,653,468,495]" class="Arachnida" family="Diplocentridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Diplocentridae</taxonomicName>
). The rock was semi-buried in the ground, under dry forest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
